sql: SELECT Name, Investor, Company, AVG(Money_Requested) FROM entrepreneur JOIN people ON entrepreneur.People_ID = people.People_ID WHERE entrepreneur.People_ID != 79 GROUP BY Name, Investor, Company;
SELECT COUNT(Money_Requested) FROM entrepreneur WHERE  People_ID = 10
SELECT AVG(people.People_ID), entrepreneur.People_ID, Company FROM entrepreneur JOIN people ON entrepreneur.People_ID = people.People_ID WHERE  Entrepreneur_ID = 54 ORDER BY Company DESC LIMIT 1
SELECT MIN(People_ID), Height FROM people WHERE Height != 96 GROUP BY Height
SELECT l.Name FROM people AS l WHERE l.Weight <= 32
SELECT j.Investor FROM entrepreneur AS j WHERE j.Money_Requested != 45 ORDER BY j.Investor ASC LIMIT 10
SELECT Name FROM people WHERE People_ID < 11 ORDER BY Name ASC;
SELECT AVG(w.People_ID), w.Height FROM people AS w WHERE w.Weight BETWEEN 86 AND 100
SELECT SUM(s.Money_Requested), s.People_ID FROM entrepreneur AS s WHERE  s.Entrepreneur_ID != 17 GROUP BY s.People_ID;
SELECT Weight, Date_of_Birth FROM people WHERE People_ID BETWEEN 1 AND 10 OR  Height != 98 ORDER BY Weight DESC LIMIT 6
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Money_Requested), Entrepreneur_ID, Investor, Company FROM entrepreneur WHERE People_ID >= 87 GROUP BY Company ORDER BY Company ASC
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Entrepreneur_ID), entrepreneur.People_ID FROM entrepreneur JOIN people ON entrepreneur.People_ID = people.People_ID WHERE  Money_Requested >= 60
SELECT Money_Requested FROM entrepreneur WHERE Money_Requested BETWEEN 1 AND 10 ORDER BY Money_Requested DESC LIMIT 4
SELECT AVG(b.Weight), b.Date_of_Birth FROM people AS b GROUP BY b.Date_of_Birth HAVING COUNT(b.People_ID) <= 71

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Investor), Company FROM entrepreneur WHERE Entrepreneur_ID BETWEEN 1 AND 10 AND Money_Requested < 13 AND People_ID IN (SELECT People_ID FROM people) GROUP BY Company HAVING MAX(Money_Requested) < 70 ORDER BY Company DESC;
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.Height), p.Name FROM people AS p WHERE p.People_ID < 73
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Height), Weight FROM people WHERE Height > 95 GROUP BY Weight HAVING MIN(Height) < 95
SELECT T1.People_ID FROM entrepreneur AS T1 INNER JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID = T2.People_ID WHERE T1.People_ID BETWEEN 1 AND 10 OR T1.Entrepreneur_ID < 13;
SELECT Entrepreneur_ID FROM entrepreneur WHERE People_ID BETWEEN 1 AND 10;
SELECT Name, Date_of_Birth FROM people WHERE Weight < 10 ORDER BY Date_of_Birth DESC LIMIT 8;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT entrepreneur.Entrepreneur_ID), entrepreneur.Money_Requested FROM entrepreneur WHERE entrepreneur.Entrepreneur_ID BETWEEN 1 AND 10 AND EXISTS (SELECT * FROM people AS r WHERE r.People_ID != 21 AND entrepreneur.People_ID = r.People_ID LIMIT 1);
SELECT COUNT(q.Money_Requested), SUM(q.Money_Requested) FROM entrepreneur AS q WHERE q.People_ID BETWEEN 1 AND 10 AND  q.People_ID < 13 LIMIT 3
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT q.Weight), q.People_ID FROM people AS q WHERE  q.People_ID < 95 ORDER BY q.People_ID DESC
SELECT Money_Requested, entrepreneur.People_ID, Company FROM entrepreneur JOIN people ON entrepreneur.People_ID = people.People_ID GROUP BY Money_Requested, entrepreneur.People_ID, Company LIMIT 4
SELECT SUM(Money_Requested), MAX(People_ID) FROM entrepreneur WHERE  Money_Requested > 25
SELECT AVG(m.Money_Requested), m.Investor FROM entrepreneur AS m WHERE  m.Money_Requested <= 62 LIMIT 2
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT q.Date_of_Birth) FROM people AS q WHERE People_ID NOT IN (SELECT People_ID FROM entrepreneur AS g WHERE  g.People_ID > 74) LIMIT 3
SELECT SUM(Money_Requested), Company FROM entrepreneur JOIN people ON entrepreneur.People_ID = people.People_ID WHERE  Weight <= 72 ORDER BY Company DESC LIMIT 1
SELECT MAX(p.Weight), p.Name FROM people AS p WHERE  p.Height != 91 ORDER BY p.Name ASC
